---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="EV Charging for Healthcare Facilities — Evium Charging"
  description="Turnkey EV charging for hospitals, medical campuses, clinics, and nursing homes. Zero operational burden, 24/7 monitoring, and zero upfront cost options."
>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════
       HERO
  ════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="relative min-h-screen flex items-center overflow-hidden bg-[#0d1c26] pt-20">

    <!-- Subtle radial glow -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none">
      <div class="absolute top-0 left-0 w-full h-full bg-[radial-gradient(ellipse_55%_60%_at_20%_50%,rgba(45,200,86,0.07),transparent)]"></div>
    </div>

    <!-- Charger image, right side -->
    <img
      src="/images/evium-evocharge-l2-wallmount.png"
      alt="Evium Level 2 Wall-Mount Charger"
      class="absolute right-0 bottom-0 h-[85%] object-contain object-bottom opacity-30 md:opacity-50 drop-shadow-[0_0_80px_rgba(45,200,86,0.15)] pointer-events-none select-none"
    />

    <!-- Diagonal overlay -->
    <div
      class="absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none"
      style="background: linear-gradient(108deg, #0d1c26 55%, transparent 55%);"
    ></div>

    <!-- Content -->
    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-6xl mx-auto w-full px-6 md:px-12 py-28">
      <p class="text-evium-green text-xs font-bold tracking-[0.22em] uppercase mb-5">EV Charging for Healthcare</p>
      <h1 class="text-white font-black leading-[1.06] mb-6" style="font-size: clamp(2.6rem, 5.5vw, 5rem);">
        Dependable Charging<br />
        for Every Person<br />
        <span class="text-evium-green">on Your Campus.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-white/55 text-lg max-w-lg mb-10 leading-relaxed">
        Staff, patients, and visitors expect reliable EV charging. Evium delivers a fully managed solution — assessment to installation to 24/7 support — with zero operational burden on your team.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 items-center">
        <a
          href="/contact/quote"
          class="inline-block bg-evium-green text-[#0d1c26] font-black text-sm tracking-widest uppercase px-8 py-4 hover:bg-white transition-colors duration-200"
        >
          Request a Site Assessment
        </a>
        <a
          href="#what-evium-delivers"
          class="inline-block text-white/65 font-semibold text-sm tracking-widest uppercase px-8 py-4 border border-white/20 hover:border-evium-green hover:text-evium-green transition-colors duration-200"
        >
          See What's Included
        </a>
      </div>

      <!-- Stats -->
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-10 mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-white/10">
        <div>
          <div class="text-evium-green font-black text-3xl">500+</div>
          <div class="text-white/40 text-xs uppercase tracking-widest mt-1">Chargers Deployed</div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="text-evium-green font-black text-3xl">24/7</div>
          <div class="text-white/40 text-xs uppercase tracking-widest mt-1">Live Monitoring & Support</div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="text-evium-green font-black text-3xl">$0</div>
          <div class="text-white/40 text-xs uppercase tracking-widest mt-1">Upfront Cost Option</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════
       WHY HEALTHCARE NEEDS EV CHARGING
  ════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="bg-evium-dark py-24 px-6 md:px-12">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-evium-green text-xs font-bold tracking-[0.22em] uppercase mb-4">The Case for EV Charging</p>
      <h2 class="text-white font-black text-3xl md:text-4xl mb-4 leading-tight">
        Why Healthcare Facilities Can't Afford to Wait
      </h2>
      <p class="text-white/50 text-base max-w-2xl mb-16 leading-relaxed">
        EV adoption among healthcare workers and patients is accelerating. Facilities that invest now are building a meaningful staff benefit and patient amenity — those that don't are falling behind.
      </p>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-evium-dark-light border border-white/8 p-7">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-evium-green/10 border border-evium-green/25 flex items-center justify-center mb-5">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-evium-green" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M17 20h5v-2a3 3 0 00-5.356-1.857M17 20H7m10 0v-2c0-.656-.126-1.283-.356-1.857M7 20H2v-2a3 3 0 015.356-1.857M7 20v-2c0-.656.126-1.283.356-1.857m0 0a5.002 5.002 0 019.288 0" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-white font-bold text-base mb-3">Staff Retention & Recruiting</h3>
          <p class="text-white/45 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Clinical talent is competitive. EV charging is a tangible, modern benefit — not a perk, a differentiator. Nurses, physicians, and technicians notice.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-evium-dark-light border border-white/8 p-7">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-evium-green/10 border border-evium-green/25 flex items-center justify-center mb-5">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-evium-green" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 8v4l3 3m6-3a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-white font-bold text-base mb-3">Long Shift Coverage</h3>
          <p class="text-white/45 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Staff working 8–12 hour shifts plug in when they arrive and leave with a full charge. Level 2 works perfectly for this dwell time — no rushing, no DC fast required.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-evium-dark-light border border-white/8 p-7">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-evium-green/10 border border-evium-green/25 flex items-center justify-center mb-5">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-evium-green" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M4.318 6.318a4.5 4.5 0 000 6.364L12 20.364l7.682-7.682a4.5 4.5 0 00-6.364-6.364L12 7.636l-1.318-1.318a4.5 4.5 0 00-6.364 0z" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-white font-bold text-base mb-3">Patient & Visitor Experience</h3>
          <p class="text-white/45 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Patients attending appointments, families on extended stays — they appreciate being able to charge without stress. It's one less thing to worry about during an already difficult time.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-evium-dark-light border border-white/8 p-7">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-evium-green/10 border border-evium-green/25 flex items-center justify-center mb-5">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-evium-green" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4M7.835 4.697a3.42 3.42 0 001.946-.806 3.42 3.42 0 014.438 0 3.42 3.42 0 001.946.806 3.42 3.42 0 013.138 3.138 3.42 3.42 0 00.806 1.946 3.42 3.42 0 010 4.438 3.42 3.42 0 00-.806 1.946 3.42 3.42 0 01-3.138 3.138 3.42 3.42 0 00-1.946.806 3.42 3.42 0 01-4.438 0 3.42 3.42 0 00-1.946-.806 3.42 3.42 0 01-3.138-3.138 3.42 3.42 0 00-.806-1.946 3.42 3.42 0 010-4.438 3.42 3.42 0 00.806-1.946 3.42 3.42 0 013.138-3.138z" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-white font-bold text-base mb-3">Institutional Credibility</h3>
          <p class="text-white/45 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Leading health systems are adding EV infrastructure as part of their sustainability commitments and LEED goals. It signals organizational leadership.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════
       RELIABILITY FIRST
  ════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="bg-[#0d1c26] py-24 px-6 md:px-12">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center">
        <div>
          <p class="text-evium-green text-xs font-bold tracking-[0.22em] uppercase mb-4">Reliability First</p>
          <h2 class="text-white font-black text-3xl md:text-4xl mb-6 leading-tight">
            In a Healthcare Environment,<br />
            <span class="text-evium-green">Downtime Is Not Acceptable.</span>
          </h2>
          <p class="text-white/50 text-base leading-relaxed mb-8">
            A charger that doesn't work reflects on your facility. Staff lose trust. Visitors are frustrated. Your facilities team gets the call. Evium is built around maximizing uptime — and minimizing the chance you ever have to deal with that.
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-4">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <span class="mt-1 w-5 h-5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-evium-green/15 border border-evium-green/30 flex items-center justify-center">
                <svg class="w-2.5 h-2.5 text-evium-green" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 8 8"><circle cx="4" cy="4" r="3"/></svg>
              </span>
              <span class="text-white/60 text-sm leading-relaxed"><strong class="text-white font-semibold">Remote diagnostics</strong> — Evium monitors every unit in real time. We know about issues before your staff does.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <span class="mt-1 w-5 h-5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-evium-green/15 border border-evium-green/30 flex items-center justify-center">
                <svg class="w-2.5 h-2.5 text-evium-green" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 8 8"><circle cx="4" cy="4" r="3"/></svg>
              </span>
              <span class="text-white/60 text-sm leading-relaxed"><strong class="text-white font-semibold">24/7 support line</strong> — multilingual, covering hardware, network, and payment issues around the clock.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <span class="mt-1 w-5 h-5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-evium-green/15 border border-evium-green/30 flex items-center justify-center">
                <svg class="w-2.5 h-2.5 text-evium-green" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 8 8"><circle cx="4" cy="4" r="3"/></svg>
              </span>
              <span class="text-white/60 text-sm leading-relaxed"><strong class="text-white font-semibold">Rapid maintenance response</strong> — when on-site intervention is needed, we dispatch quickly and document everything.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-4">
              <span class="mt-1 w-5 h-5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-evium-green/15 border border-evium-green/30 flex items-center justify-center">
                <svg class="w-2.5 h-2.5 text-evium-green" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 8 8"><circle cx="4" cy="4" r="3"/></svg>
              </span>
              <span class="text-white/60 text-sm leading-relaxed"><strong class="text-white font-semibold">OCPP 1.6+ open protocol</strong> — not locked into proprietary networks. Your infrastructure remains flexible and future-proof.</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <div class="bg-evium-dark-light border border-white/8 p-6 flex flex-col">
            <div class="text-evium-green font-black text-4xl mb-1">99%+</div>
            <div class="text-white/40 text-xs uppercase tracking-widest leading-tight">Target Network Uptime</div>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-evium-dark-light border border-white/8 p-6 flex flex-col">
            <div class="text-evium-green font-black text-4xl mb-1">24/7</div>
            <div class="text-white/40 text-xs uppercase tracking-widest leading-tight">Active Monitoring</div>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-evium-dark-light border border-white/8 p-6 flex flex-col col-span-2">
            <div class="text-evium-green font-black text-4xl mb-1">Remote-First</div>
            <div class="text-white/40 text-xs uppercase tracking-widest leading-tight">Most Issues Resolved Without a Site Visit</div>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-evium-dark-light border border-evium-green/20 p-6 flex flex-col col-span-2">
            <p class="text-white/55 text-sm leading-relaxed italic">
              "We needed a partner who would own the problem, not hand it back to us. Evium monitors everything — we've never had to call them first."
            </p>
            <span class="text-white/30 text-xs mt-3 not-italic">— Facilities Director, Regional Medical Center</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════
       LONG DWELL TIMES
  ════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="bg-evium-dark py-24 px-6 md:px-12">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center">
        <div class="order-2 lg:order-1">
          <div class="bg-evium-dark-light border border-white/8 p-8">
            <div class="text-white/30 text-xs uppercase tracking-widest mb-6">Typical Dwell Time vs. Level 2 Charge Time</div>
            <div class="space-y-5">
              <div>
                <div class="flex justify-between items-center mb-1.5">
                  <span class="text-white/65 text-sm">Clinical Staff (8–12 hr shift)</span>
                  <span class="text-evium-green font-bold text-sm">Full Charge</span>
                </div>
                <div class="h-2 bg-white/8 rounded-full overflow-hidden">
                  <div class="h-full bg-evium-green rounded-full" style="width: 100%;"></div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div>
                <div class="flex justify-between items-center mb-1.5">
                  <span class="text-white/65 text-sm">Long-Procedure Patients (4–6 hrs)</span>
                  <span class="text-evium-green font-bold text-sm">~80% Charge</span>
                </div>
                <div class="h-2 bg-white/8 rounded-full overflow-hidden">
                  <div class="h-full bg-evium-green rounded-full" style="width: 80%;"></div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div>
                <div class="flex justify-between items-center mb-1.5">
                  <span class="text-white/65 text-sm">Outpatient Visits (1.5–2.5 hrs)</span>
                  <span class="text-white/40 font-bold text-sm">~30–40% Charge</span>
                </div>
                <div class="h-2 bg-white/8 rounded-full overflow-hidden">
                  <div class="h-full bg-evium-green/40 rounded-full" style="width: 35%;"></div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div>
                <div class="flex justify-between items-center mb-1.5">
                  <span class="text-white/65 text-sm">Extended Family Stays (12+ hrs)</span>
                  <span class="text-evium-green font-bold text-sm">Full Charge</span>
                </div>
                <div class="h-2 bg-white/8 rounded-full overflow-hidden">
                  <div class="h-full bg-evium-green rounded-full" style="width: 100%;"></div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-white/30 text-xs mt-6 leading-relaxed">
              Based on a standard Level 2 charger at ~7.2 kW. Average EV battery depleted ~50% = ~35 kWh to fill. Approximate figures.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="order-1 lg:order-2">
          <p class="text-evium-green text-xs font-bold tracking-[0.22em] uppercase mb-4">Long Dwell Times</p>
          <h2 class="text-white font-black text-3xl md:text-4xl mb-6 leading-tight">
            Healthcare Has the Best Utilization Rates in the Industry.
          </h2>
          <p class="text-white/50 text-base leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Long dwell times are a feature, not a problem. When a nurse parks for a 12-hour shift, a Level 2 charger delivers a complete charge without any DC fast infrastructure needed. This means lower installation cost and exceptional value per session.
          </p>
          <p class="text-white/50 text-base leading-relaxed">
            For high-volume visitor areas like drop-off zones or short-stay spaces, Evium can optionally integrate DC fast charging — but for most healthcare parking, Level 2 is the right call economically and operationally.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════
       WHAT EVIUM DELIVERS
  ════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section id="what-evium-delivers" class="bg-[#0d1c26] py-24 px-6 md:px-12">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-evium-green text-xs font-bold tracking-[0.22em] uppercase mb-4">Complete Turnkey Service</p>
      <h2 class="text-white font-black text-3xl md:text-4xl mb-4 leading-tight">
        Everything Handled. Nothing Left for Your Team.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-white/50 text-base max-w-2xl mb-16 leading-relaxed">
        Facility managers and operations teams have enough to manage. Evium owns the entire lifecycle — from site walk to ongoing support — so EV charging never becomes your problem.
      </p>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-px bg-white/8">
        <div class="bg-[#0d1c26] p-8">
          <div class="text-evium-green font-black text-lg mb-1">01</div>
          <h3 class="text-white font-bold text-base mb-3">Site Assessment</h3>
          <p class="text-white/45 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            We evaluate your existing electrical capacity, parking layout, and usage patterns across staff and visitor zones. No cost, no commitment.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-[#0d1c26] p-8">
          <div class="text-evium-green font-black text-lg mb-1">02</div>
          <h3 class="text-white font-bold text-base mb-3">Hardware Selection</h3>
          <p class="text-white/45 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            We recommend the right mix — wall-mount L2 for garages, pedestal L2 for surface lots, optional DC fast for high-traffic visitor areas.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-[#0d1c26] p-8">
          <div class="text-evium-green font-black text-lg mb-1">03</div>
          <h3 class="text-white font-bold text-base mb-3">Permits & Compliance</h3>
          <p class="text-white/45 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            We manage all electrical permits, utility coordination, and applicable ADA accessibility requirements. You sign off; we handle the paperwork.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-[#0d1c26] p-8">
          <div class="text-evium-green font-black text-lg mb-1">04</div>
          <h3 class="text-white font-bold text-base mb-3">Installation with Minimal Disruption</h3>
          <p class="text-white/45 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Our crews are experienced in active healthcare environments. We schedule around shift changes, avoid high-traffic hours, and keep noise and disruption to a minimum.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-[#0d1c26] p-8">
          <div class="text-evium-green font-black text-lg mb-1">05</div>
          <h3 class="text-white font-bold text-base mb-3">Access Control & Software Setup</h3>
          <p class="text-white/45 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            RFID cards or app-based access for staff. Open payment for visitors. Separate pricing tiers configurable per zone or lot. Revenue and usage reporting via your owner portal.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-[#0d1c26] p-8">
          <div class="text-evium-green font-black text-lg mb-1">06</div>
          <h3 class="text-white font-bold text-base mb-3">Ongoing Monitoring & Maintenance</h3>
          <p class="text-white/45 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            24/7 remote monitoring with real-time alerts, remote diagnostics, and rapid dispatch for any on-site issues. You don't manage chargers — we do.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════
       ACCESS CONTROL
  ════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="bg-evium-dark py-24 px-6 md:px-12">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-start">
        <div>
          <p class="text-evium-green text-xs font-bold tracking-[0.22em] uppercase mb-4">Staff & Visitor Access Control</p>
          <h2 class="text-white font-black text-3xl md:text-4xl mb-6 leading-tight">
            Different Rules for<br />Different Zones.
          </h2>
          <p class="text-white/50 text-base leading-relaxed mb-8">
            Staff parking and visitor parking have different needs. Evium's platform lets you define separate access rules, pricing tiers, and subsidy programs — all managed from one portal, with no IT integration required.
          </p>
          <div class="space-y-5">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-5">
              <div class="mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-evium-green/10 border border-evium-green/25 flex items-center justify-center">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-evium-green" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M15 7a2 2 0 012 2m4 0a6 6 0 01-7.743 5.743L11 17H9v2H7v2H4a1 1 0 01-1-1v-2.586a1 1 0 01.293-.707l5.964-5.964A6 6 0 1121 9z" />
                </svg>
              </div>
              <div>
                <div class="text-white font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Staff Access</div>
                <p class="text-white/45 text-sm leading-relaxed">RFID card or Evium app authentication. Subsidized or fully free charging for employees — your HR team sets the benefit level, the portal enforces it.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-5">
              <div class="mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-evium-green/10 border border-evium-green/25 flex items-center justify-center">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-evium-green" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M3 10h18M7 15h1m4 0h1m-7 4h12a3 3 0 003-3V8a3 3 0 00-3-3H6a3 3 0 00-3 3v8a3 3 0 003 3z" />
                </svg>
              </div>
              <div>
                <div class="text-white font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Visitor Access</div>
                <p class="text-white/45 text-sm leading-relaxed">Credit card or contactless payment. No app download required. Set your own per-kWh or per-hour rate. Revenue flows directly to your account.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-5">
              <div class="mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-evium-green/10 border border-evium-green/25 flex items-center justify-center">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-evium-green" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 17v-2m3 2v-4m3 4v-6m2 10H7a2 2 0 01-2-2V5a2 2 0 012-2h5.586a1 1 0 01.707.293l5.414 5.414a1 1 0 01.293.707V19a2 2 0 01-2 2z" />
                </svg>
              </div>
              <div>
                <div class="text-white font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Owner Portal Reporting</div>
                <p class="text-white/45 text-sm leading-relaxed">Real-time session data, utilization by zone, revenue breakdown, and energy consumption — all accessible through your portal with exportable reports.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-evium-dark-light border border-white/8 p-8">
          <div class="text-white/30 text-xs uppercase tracking-widest mb-6">Example: 200-Bed Community Hospital</div>
          <div class="space-y-6">
